      "scoring_710502": "SCORINGDimension ItemsIntrinsic, Health Concerns 1, 5, 9, 13, 17Intrinsic, Self-Control 2, 6, 10, 14, 18Extrinsic, Immediate Reinforcement 3, 7, 11, 15, 19Extrinsic, Social Pressure 4, 8, 12, 16, 20COMPUTATIONWe score the scaled as average ratings across the relevant sub-dimension items. Items with missing ratings can be excluded from the denominator. For example, the health concerns score = Sum of items (1 + 5 + 9 + 13 + 17)/5If item #9 is missing data, the calculation would be the sum of items (1 + 5 + 13 + 17)/4Level of intrinsic relative to extrinsic motivation is calculated as a difference score with the extrinsic scale score subtracted from the intrinsic score."
